    <RacerFolder id="1248" parentID="1057" level="2" writerID="0" creatorID="0" nodeType="1246" template="1050" sortOrder="2" createDate="2013-05-13T19:32:41" updateDate="2013-05-27T19:10:29" nodeName="Respected Racers" urlName="respected-racers" writerName="Rob" creatorName="Rob" path="-1,1057,1248" isDoc="">
      <bodyText><![CDATA[
<p>As I've competed on iRacing I've come across many drivers with
different approaches to racing. &nbsp;Here I've recognised some of
them for better or worse. &nbsp;Of course, expereinces and opinions
vary but this is&nbsp;<strong>my</strong> list. Based on
<strong>my</strong> experiences. &nbsp;If a driver is on the No
list, he's been either consistently poor or done something
extremley stupid like drive around the track backwards or wait for
drivers to come by and then crash them. &nbsp;</p>

<p>The Yo list is only made up of drivers I'ved race closely and
had first hand experience with. &nbsp;They've left enough of an
impression that I'd be happy to race with them again any time, and
happy to leave plenty of room to ensure we all have a good time.
&nbsp;I trust them to return any courteousy I offer. The No list is
mostly drivers I've diced with on track whom I have first
hand-experience of their style of racing, or they've done something
massively stupid and it has caused serious and rage on voice and
I've seen the effects first hand.</p>

<p>&nbsp;</p>

<p>Click on the driver name to see their iRacing profile and
statistics. &nbsp;Hover over the driver name to see my
comments.</p>

<?UMBRACO_MACRO macroAlias="RespectedRacers" />]]></bodyText>
