            <bodyText><![CDATA[
<p><img src="/media/296/laguna-seca-track-map.jpg" width="400" height="284" alt="Laguna Track Map" style="float: right;"/>Week two in the Star Mazda
series was looking good for me. &nbsp;I performed well in early
practice and got my times down to the high 1:19's (1:19.8 was my
best), which was plenty fast enough to do well in any race I was to
land in, especially given I'm in the wrong timezone for the really
high SOF races.</p>

<p>Qualifying for Laguna Seca was a bit out of order. &nbsp;Usually
I qualify before I race, in an effort to keep out of the riffraff.
&nbsp;This time I was really enjoying Laguna Seca and was
consistent, and my mate Andrew Kiss was racing too so I thought I'd
jump straight in and race. &nbsp;I did qualifying before the second
race.</p>

<p>Here's my qualifying lap of 1:20.066. &nbsp;I went a few tenths
faster in practice, but what can you do? It was still pretty fast
:)</p>

<?UMBRACO_MACRO videourl="" videoheight=""
aspectratio="" allowfullscreen="0" videowidth=""
macroAlias="uTube.ClassicPlayer" videoid="5oxull4XXlQ" />


<p>&nbsp;</p>

<h3>Race 1&nbsp;<a href="/media/261/laguna-r1.jpg"
class="btn btn-mini btn-primary">View the results</a></h3>

<p>I had my first race on Thursday night, before I had qualified;
something I try to avoid. &nbsp;I started from 6th place and was up
to third by the first corner, and looking good to slot into either
2nd or 1st by the time I'd exitted the corner. &nbsp;Alas, my old
mate Andrew Kiss was also right there battling for position and we
touched. &nbsp;Possibly I turned in on him or possibly he tapped me
in the rear, amid the first corner carnage. &nbsp;Had I qualified I
would have been on pole for sure and would have avoided this
mess.</p>

<p>That put me back to 7th, but I was able to quickly rise up the
field as other cars fell off and I also lapped faster than any
other car on circuit. &nbsp;I was in 2nd and closing on 1st when I
made a mistake on the run out of turn 6 and ran nose first into the
left tyre barrier. &nbsp;Fortuantely my car had no major handling
problems and I was able to continue, with only a loss of time to
the leader.</p>

<p>I finished the race in 2nd place, down 19 seconds on the leader,
after closing from a 24s deficit earlier on.</p>

<?UMBRACO_MACRO videourl="" videoheight=""
aspectratio="" allowfullscreen="0" videowidth=""
macroAlias="uTube.ClassicPlayer" videoid="dPPXbLMqvy0" />


<p>&nbsp;</p>

<p>&nbsp;</p>

<h3>Race 2&nbsp;<a href="/media/266/laguna-r2.jpg"
class="btn btn-mini btn-primary">View the results</a></h3>

<?UMBRACO_MACRO videourl="" videoheight=""
aspectratio="" allowfullscreen="0" videowidth=""
macroAlias="uTube.ClassicPlayer" videoid="P3IDmWN0Q5Q" />


<p><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>

<p>Race 2 was a was promising. &nbsp;I qualified in fourth position
and made a decent start, running in second place until Steve Owen
hit me on my left rear tyre while approaching the final turn of lap
7 and bent my suspension, putting me out of the race. &nbsp;He went
on, undamaged, to second place.</p>

<p>It was an annoying turn of events because Steve Owen is perhaps
one of my main competitors for overall division 4 championship
honours. &nbsp;We were to battle a few more times during the week.
&nbsp;I took a SR and iRating hit as well as lost valuable
championship points. &nbsp;From the look of the replay, it wasn't
Steve's fault. &nbsp;It appeared as if he didn't even touch my car,
or if he did, it was the slightest of touches.</p>

<p>&nbsp;</p>

<p>&nbsp;</p>

<h3>Race 3&nbsp;<a href="/media/271/laguna-r3.jpg"
class="btn btn-mini btn-primary">View the results</a></h3>

<?UMBRACO_MACRO videourl="" videoheight=""
aspectratio="" allowfullscreen="0" videowidth=""
macroAlias="uTube.ClassicPlayer" videoid="DMuop_S6V1E" />


<p>&nbsp;</p>

<p>Again, not the best of races. &nbsp;This time I lined up again
in fourth position, immediately behind Paul Ezerski, the winner of
the last race. &nbsp;This time, as the replay shows and Paul
himself admitted, Paul took off from the line in reverse gear
instead of first! &nbsp;When I saw Paul wasn't going foward and I
made another awesome start, my reflexes kicked in and jinked to the
left nearly taking out David Buda who started from fifth. &nbsp;We
didn't touch, but my right rear touch Paul's car and it was enough
to bend my suspension and I vered straight off the road into the
wall well before the first turn. &nbsp;Race over before I even
crossed the start/finish line to behind the first lap!</p>

<p>&nbsp;</p>

<p>&nbsp;</p>

<h3>Race 4&nbsp;<a href="/media/276/laguna-r4.jpg"
class="btn btn-mini btn-primary">View the results</a></h3>

<p>Races don't always go to plan. &nbsp;this time I started from
sixth place, in a very high SOF of 2763, possible the strongest
field I've ever raced in. &nbsp;I was running well, in fourth place
with a clear gap to fifth, when I dropped the rear coming out of
turn 4. &nbsp;Something I only ever did that once in all the races
and practice sessions I did at Laguna Seca this week. &nbsp;What
bad timing! &nbsp;I did battle with Sam Clark a bit during the race
and would continue that battle in a more races to come during the
week.</p>

<p>I still wasn't satisfied and I knew I had more speed and good
results and really wanted to get some good runs on the board.
&nbsp;I had to race again!</p>

<p>&nbsp;</p>

<p>&nbsp;</p>

<h3>Race 5&nbsp;<a href="/media/281/laguna-r5.jpg"
class="btn btn-mini btn-primary">View the results</a></h3>

<?UMBRACO_MACRO videourl="" videoheight=""
aspectratio="" allowfullscreen="0" videowidth=""
macroAlias="uTube.ClassicPlayer" videoid="wy9CIHNokvw" />


<p>Ok this was now getting crazy. &nbsp;I qualified 2nd and made a
good solid start and was sitting pretty in 3rd place for the first
dozon or so laps, unable to pass Steve Owen but not losing ground
to him when I dropped it at the bottom of the corkscrew and hit the
wall on the right hand side. &nbsp;I limped back to the pits for
repairs and was able to keep going. &nbsp;Two other drivers fell
off the track as the race progressed and I was able to salvage 7th
place and 54 points from a 2238 SOF race.</p>

<p>&nbsp;</p>

<p>&nbsp;</p>

<h3>Race 6&nbsp;<a href="/media/286/laguna-r6.jpg"
class="btn btn-mini btn-primary">View the results</a></h3>

<?UMBRACO_MACRO videourl="" videoheight=""
aspectratio="" allowfullscreen="0" videowidth=""
macroAlias="uTube.ClassicPlayer" videoid="3vnO-sC1iGE" />


<p>Surely my luck had to change soon, and this race looked like
being the race! &nbsp;I qualified on pole and was led out strongly.
&nbsp;Unfortunatley it was a little too strongly and I again lost
it on the exit of turn 6. &nbsp;The rear of the car jumped out a
bit, as it usually does. &nbsp;I corrected, as I usually do.
&nbsp;Unfortunately this time I correct too much for the slide and
the car bit and took off to the right and I smashed into the tyre.
Race over when I had a good chance of the win.</p>

<p>It just wasn't sitting right with me. &nbsp;I could feel that I
had a better result in me and I desparately wanted to get that race
win at Laguna Seca. &nbsp;I knew I could do it. I thought just one
more race... &nbsp;This would be my last chance to race this week
anyway.</p>

<p>&nbsp;</p>

<p>&nbsp;</p>

<h3>Race 7&nbsp;<a href="/media/291/laguna-r7.jpg"
class="btn btn-mini btn-primary">View the results</a></h3>

<p>This is it, my final chance. &nbsp;I lined up on pole, with a
1.4s advantage over second place, and ranked #7. &nbsp;I was pumped
for a good result. &nbsp;The race was rather boring all in all.
&nbsp;2nd place put up a decent fight for the first few laps but
then dropped off to an over 10 second gap, which was all I needed
to provide a safety buffer, where I could drive well within my
limits. &nbsp;The remainder of the race was about managing that
gap. &nbsp;When I needed to I'd put in the a fast lap and pull out
2seconds. &nbsp;Otherwise I was just cruising, braking early and
getting on the gas late. &nbsp;</p>

<p>It was a good win, also setting the fastest lap of the race, and
my fastest race lap of the week, a lap slightly faster than my
qualifying time from last season! &nbsp;I also finished the race
with 0 incidents.</p>

<p>&nbsp;</p>

<p>&nbsp;</p>

<p>So far this season I've had at least one win from every race!
&nbsp;Coolness. Next week is Road Atlanta, my first bad race from
last season. I'm looking to obviously do better there this season
and make up for a bad Laguna Seca this week. &nbsp;I've got limited
running time next week though, so I'll have to get my racing in
early...</p>
]]></bodyText>
