            <bodyText><![CDATA[
<p>Round 2 of the 2012 season 3 is at the Laguna Seca circuit in
California, famous for the mighty corkscrew turn. &nbsp;It's also
the location of my first Star Mazda victory (I was lucky in that
the fastest guy dropped connection and allowing me to ran rampant
on the rest of the field. &nbsp;He did rejoin, a few laps down and
proceded to go like stink).</p>

<p>During practice so far this week I've managed to log a few mid
to low 1:20's until last night when I increased my tyre pressures
by 2psi all round and immediately dipped into the 1:19's, with a
1:19.945. &nbsp;I was going even faster on the next lap before I
spun, at which point I ended my practice session for the evening.
&nbsp;It's a good sign that the faster pace is there. &nbsp;This
time is also 2nd fastest in my division qualifying and top 20
overall in the world. &nbsp;While many, including myself, have not
yet qualified, this is a postive for the rest of the
week.&nbsp;</p>

<p>A lot of drivers hate Laguna Seca, but I enjoy it so I'm hoping
for some strong results later in the week.</p>

<p><img src="/media/162/iracingresultspracticesession_ls.jpg" width="800" height="365" alt="Iracingresultspracticesession _ls"/>&nbsp;</p>

<p><br />
 Here are the qualifying times for my division (Divisions are based
on the iRating of people and are indicative of overall speed)</p>

<p><img src="/media/167/qualifying-2012s3r2-sofar.png" width="496" height="608" alt="Qualifying-2012s3r2-sofar"/></p>
]]></bodyText>
