            <bodyText><![CDATA[
<p><img src="/media/406/roadamericamap.png" width="400" height="256" alt="Roadamericamap" style="float: right;"/>Road
America and week 3 of season 3 2012 of the Star Mazda series is now
done and dusted and I can reflect back on a great week. &nbsp;I'm
not sure why, but I got really hooked up this week, mixing it with
the big boys. &nbsp;The guys I did battle with had iRatings up and
over 4000, so it was extremely satisfying that I could mix it with
them race after race and over the course of a 20 lap race lose
barely 5 seconds. &nbsp;At one race, after a few races together
Danny Kane asked me what my &nbsp;iRating was and was shocked it
was so low. &nbsp;ha!</p>

<p>I also had guys doing 2:03.8's on low downforce setups try my
high downforce setup and comment that they never thought it was
possible to go so fast on a high downforce set, after running
2:03.9's, with me doing 2:04.1's, with an optimal of 2:03.4</p>

<p>My biggest downfall was the number of races I had where I got
messed up by someone whilst in high SOF races. &nbsp;If not for
that I'd definitely be over 2000 iRating. &nbsp;At least I got my A
class license back :)</p>

<p>I think I did a record (at least for this season) 11 races this
week in my bid to crack 2000 iRating. In the end I was worried
about getting a bad result that would hurt my points, so I
stopped.</p>

<p>At one point my win rate for this season was 50%. &nbsp;Now it's
about 25% (5 wins from 19 races).</p>

<p>I also didn't qualify before my first few races, again!
&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>Race 1</strong></p>

<p>The first race at Road America was unofficial, and I was left to
do 20 laps by myself lol. &nbsp;At least I got to know the track in
race spec and got to know that 6 gallons wont last the full race
distance (stopping just after the last corner)</p>

<p>&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>Race 2&nbsp;<a href="/media/361/roadamerica-r1.PNG">View
the results</a></strong></p>

<?UMBRACO_MACRO videourl="" videoheight=""
aspectratio="" allowfullscreen="0" videowidth=""
macroAlias="uTube.ClassicPlayer" videoid="f4HjBQiJWjA" />


<p><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>

<p>I started 12th, after not qualifying and made good progress,
getting up to 4th before Milko Tas had an off and then rejoined the
track on the racing line, moving very slowly. &nbsp;I had to go
wide to avoid him and I put my wheels into the dirt and dropped it.
&nbsp;Race over.</p>

<p>&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>Race 3</strong></p>

<p>Another unofficial race. &nbsp;This time I got out before
turning a lap.</p>

<p>&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>Race 4&nbsp;<a href="/media/366/roadamericaR4.PNG">View
the results</a></strong></p>

<p>Another good strong SOF (1993) and this time I started 8th,
after not qualifying. &nbsp; Worse, Junior Yearwood didn't bother
slowing down for turn 1 on the opening lap and plowed straight into
Sofia Stella who was right beside me going into turn 1. &nbsp;The
move must have scared Luke Dowding because he ran straight up my
backside, ending my race before I started to turn for the first
corner!</p>

<p>&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>

<p><strong>Race 5&nbsp;<a href="/media/371/roadamericaR5.PNG">View
the results</a></strong></p>

<p>This time I qualified (SOF 1535). &nbsp;And I started from pole!
&nbsp;Mike Quayle was right along side me, but I was feeling ok
about that because he's a good fair racer (3300 iRating too).
&nbsp;I led from pole and was never bothered. &nbsp;A good race and
a rewarding win to beat Mike fair and square (who beat me fair and
square by 6 seconds in Brands Hatch this season).</p>

<p>&nbsp;</p>

<p>&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>Race 6&nbsp;<a href="/media/376/roadamericaR6.PNG">View
the results</a></strong></p>

<p>Ah my old mate Paul Nelson, the iRacing bot. &nbsp;He does about
8 races a day, every day, and as a result pretty easily recoups
losses to SR and iRating. &nbsp;Last I checked he was on 1400
iRating and 2.5 ish SR with a B class (after being an A class
driver all last season). &nbsp;By the end of this week he had his
SR back up to 4.99 A class and iRating up to 2800. Anyway, He does
run a little faster than me, but not by a much when you consider
the amount of time he puts in. &nbsp;</p>

<p>The real threat was also going to be the Pro driver Riku Alatalo
(iRating 5111). &nbsp;He started from the pits and was charging
hard. I yielded to him on about lap 13-14 I think, not wanting to
come off trying to stay in front, when I knew he'd eventually get
me. &nbsp;The race was pretty intense while I tried to stay in
front of him and not make mistakes. &nbsp;A satisfying third place
ina &nbsp;2177 SOF race.</p>

<p>&nbsp;</p>

<p>&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>Race 7&nbsp;<a href="/media/381/roadamericaR7.PNG">View
the results</a></strong></p>

<p>I was running a solid 5th place after starting 9th, sitting on
the back of Miguel Angel3, after hunting him down over 5 or 6 laps
or so, when I dropped it. &nbsp;I manged to get back to the pits
and then set up trying to minimize the damage. &nbsp;While I did
finish 2 laps down at least I increased my iRating just. &nbsp;My
race time of 2:05.841 would have put me fourth, ahead of Miguel
Angel3 by race end.</p>

<?UMBRACO_MACRO videourl="" videoheight=""
aspectratio="" allowfullscreen="0" videowidth=""
macroAlias="uTube.ClassicPlayer" videoid="8IXQ8K_jehI" />


<p>&nbsp;</p>

<p>&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>Race 8&nbsp;<a href="/media/386/roadamericaR8.PNG">View
the results</a></strong></p>

<p>Maybe my strongest ever SOF race of 2903 saw me racing against
another Pro, Troy Schulz (5848). I started 8th but this time I got
mugged as by cars coming up behind me. I think Robert Jones5 tapped
me coming into turn 1 and then bombed dived up the inside of turn 3
on the opening lap. &nbsp;That move spun me back to last place and
I set about recovering before two spins on the same lap put me in
the pits for repairs. I eventually finished 10th, with a +1 to my
iRating, the same as last race.</p>

<?UMBRACO_MACRO videourl="" videoheight=""
aspectratio="" allowfullscreen="0" videowidth=""
macroAlias="uTube.ClassicPlayer" videoid="jfA2T8F1Exk" />


<p>&nbsp;</p>

<p>&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>Race 9&nbsp;<a href="/media/391/roadamericaR9.PNG">View
the results</a></strong></p>

<p>No way was I giving up that easily. I had pace to spare and in
this 2399 SOF race I showed it. Starting form 3rd, I pressured Mark
Ursel (4099) for the opening few laps until he locked the brakes
into turn 3, running wide and giving me the gap I needed to duck
through into 2nd. &nbsp;From there I was never headed, finishing 6
seconds behind Marcel Fachini (4139). &nbsp;It was a pretty boring
race once Mark made his mistake. I think he was catching me through
the middle of th race but I was able to open up a couple of seconds
in the last few laps.</p>

<?UMBRACO_MACRO videourl="" videoheight=""
aspectratio="" allowfullscreen="0" videowidth=""
macroAlias="uTube.ClassicPlayer" videoid="CwLK9w3ZyVQ" />


<p>&nbsp;</p>

<p>&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>Race 10&nbsp;<a
href="/media/396/roadamericaR10.PNG">View the
results</a></strong></p>

<p>This race was great fun. &nbsp;I staretd 5th and ran with top 3
for a long time, sitting right on Danny Kane's gearbox, until a
mistake of mine spun me off and I had to recover. &nbsp;I changed
back up through the field and finished just 0.1 of a second behind
David Buda. &nbsp;In the closing laps I was catching at over a
second a lap and it was pretty intense. &nbsp;As we crossed the
line David himself commented that he felt he should move over and
let me by just because I put in such a mega drive. &nbsp;My fastest
lap of the race as not far off two of the top three guys, showing I
had pletty of pace. Also this was a 20 car field.
&nbsp;Massive!</p>

<?UMBRACO_MACRO videourl="" videoheight=""
aspectratio="" allowfullscreen="0" videowidth=""
macroAlias="uTube.ClassicPlayer" videoid="qK5ysvTO-LY" />


<p>&nbsp;</p>

<p>&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>Race 11&nbsp;<a
href="/media/401/roadamericaR11.PNG">View the
results</a></strong></p>

<p>My final race of the week. &nbsp;I just had to do another to try
and increase my iRating and crack 2000. I only had 30 to go...</p>

<p>I came into the race ranked #4 and started 4th on the grid.
&nbsp;For the opening few laps I sat right on the geardboxes of the
leading 3 cars; they weren't getting away. Things were looking
good. &nbsp;Then I dropped it :( &nbsp;Race over, and Andrew Kiss
beat me by dint of finishing, lol.</p>
]]></bodyText>
