            <bodyText><![CDATA[
<p>Multiple monitors are a must have for any serious sim racer but
you don't need to shell out serious dollars for this.&nbsp;</p>

<p>The simplest and most expensive way to run multiple monitors is
to purchase a high end ATI or nVidia card and run either EyeFinity
or Surround, with multiple monitors of the same size and
resolution. &nbsp;It's possible to use the one card for three or
more monitors by using the Display Port link.</p>

<p>There is a cheaper method, although not quite as plug-and-play
as the out of the box solutions. &nbsp;The following method allows
the use of existing old monitors. &nbsp;The solution hinges on the
free&nbsp;<a
href="http://www.kegetys.fi/SoftTH/">SoftTH</a>&nbsp;(soft triple
header) program, which provides multiple monitor support in games
and allows more than two monitors to be used by adding another
cheaper video card.</p>

<p>My own setup utilises three older 19" 4:3 monitors (2 DVI and 1
VGA) and a 24" DVI monitor. I use a Radeon HD5850 card for my main
and an nVidia 8400GS to provide the ability to connect two more
monitors. &nbsp;SoftTH uses the GPU of only the main card (HD 5850)
for processing, so you may as well run the cheapest possible card
as your secondary (Ideally I'd use a more powerful main card, but
of course... :)).</p>

<p>This allows me to run a resolution of 3968x1200. &nbsp;Yes, I
lose a few pixels on the 19"'s but its worth it. &nbsp;The other
problem is that the 19"'s have a different dot pitch than the 24,
so the picture never perfectly lines up, but it's close.</p>

<p><img src="/media/1173/406383_10150558345078055_2058695515_n_600x450.jpg" width="500" height="375" alt="cheaptriplemonitors"/></p>

<p>For iRacing I use 100% the softTH configuration
and&nbsp;<strong>not</strong>&nbsp;the bezel management tool within
iRacing. &nbsp; <a
href="http://isimstation.net/community/modules/smartsection/item.php?com_mode=nest&amp;com_order=1&amp;itemid=10">
This guide</a>&nbsp;has the low down on configuring softTH.</p>

<p>I run my fourth monitor off the final VGA port on my 8400GS.
&nbsp;I use it for iSpeed and F1Speed.</p>

<p>&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>Installing SoftTH</strong></p>

<p>SoftTH is a dll and ini file that sits in the directory of each
game you want to enable softTH support for. &nbsp;When configured,
it provides extra resolution for selection. &nbsp;SoftTH is a
DirectX 9 compatiable program, so all your games will have to run
in DirectX 9 to take advantage of it. &nbsp;Hopefully this isn't a
showstopper for people and certainly in iRacing I don't notice the
difference. &nbsp;Games that focus more on gloss, like Codemasters
F1 201x series may lose comparitively more of it's lustre.</p>

<p>Download the latest version (2.08b at the time of writtting -
and it hasn't changed in two years) from&nbsp;<a
href="http://www.kegetys.fi/forum/index.php?topic=2123.0">here</a>.
Ignore the alpha wording. &nbsp;I've been running it for 18 months
and it's rock solid&nbsp;</p>
]]></bodyText>
            <teaser><![CDATA[
<p>Multiple monitors are a must have for any serious sim racer but
you don't need to shell out serious dollars for this. &nbsp; Use
SoftTH to utilise older monitors in your setup.</p>
]]></teaser>
