            <bodyText><![CDATA[
<p><img src="/media/77/s3-2012 launch.png" width="800" height="270" alt="S 3-2012 Launch" style="display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;"/>&nbsp;</p>

<p>iRacing's Season 3 for 2012 begins today, with the Star Mazdas
taking to Brands Hatch in England for round one of the twelve round
season. &nbsp;This season I've made up my own paint, with the my
work, Charm Health, as primary sponsor. I've also got Microsoft on
the engine cover, with my fuel sponsor BP on the nose. The paint
scheme is Charm Healths</p>

<p>Last season over 1500 competitors took place in the Star Mazda
series and I finished 77th overall, competing in Division 3.
&nbsp;This season I'll be in division 4 and I'm hoping to do a
little better than last season, now I know most of the tracks and
the car.</p>

<p>Star Mazdas are open-wheel race cars running on slick tyres and
using the Mazda 13B rotary engine, generating about 220HP. They're
the third step up on the open wheel road series which starts at the
MX-5 and continues with the Skip Barber car before the Star Mazda.
&nbsp;The Star Mazda is the first open wheel slick tyred car
drivers will experience as they attempt to rise up through the
ranks to race in the Formula 1 World Series.</p>
]]></bodyText>
