            <bodyText><![CDATA[
<p>Week 5 of the third season of 2012 in the Star Mazda
championship saw the teams head over to northern United States and
the Mid Ohio track. &nbsp;This was my second race at this circuit,
having raced here last season. &nbsp;Ok, that's not entirely true;
I have raced here before a few times in the Skip Barber. &nbsp;</p>

<p>Overall I had a pretty decent weekend from my 6 races.
&nbsp;Unfortunately unlike the last round I didn't have a trouble
free run, getting tagged by a few people in a few races, as well as
a few unforced errors from myself. &nbsp;</p>

<p>Those aside, I managed to increase my iRating to 2245 and my
Safety Rating to 4.68 A class. It's never been higher. &nbsp;Unlike
Phillip Island I also notched up another win. That's 6 wins from
five tracks now. &nbsp;&nbsp;</p>

<p>&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>Qualifying</strong></p>

<p>Qualifying wasn't too bad. &nbsp;I was running low 1:19.3's in
practice fair consistently but the best I could manage in
qualifying was a 1:19.6. &nbsp;I was being my normal cautious self,
not wanting to get incidents.</p>

<?UMBRACO_MACRO videourl="" videoheight=""
aspectratio="" allowfullscreen="0" videowidth=""
macroAlias="uTube.ClassicPlayer" videoid="Ub2Fdi4DQJw" />


<p>&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>Race 1</strong></p>

<p>I got reemed off the start. &nbsp;Augusto Ignaczuk decided he
would take the racing line through turn one on the opening lap,
when cars are going to be at least 2 wide AND a car (me) was right
in front. &nbsp;The result was his front left touched my rear right
and he moved over to the apex and we touched. &nbsp; It was enough
to slow me down and knock me off kilter a bit and Adam Surplice
behind me ran up my rear sending up both into a spin and he took
out a few cars behind him. &nbsp;</p>

<p>At least it gave me an opportunity to put some moves on other
cars, from pretty much last place. &nbsp;I moved up through pack,
avoiding some bad driving from Donovan Stanford, who was driving
both aggressively and far too sedately. &nbsp;On some corners (eg
turn 2) he was braking too late and on others, such as the more
challening turn 3 he was braking very early. &nbsp;He took out
another driver on turn 2 and then on the same lap caught me by
surprise by braking about 25 meters too early on turn 3 and I had
to jink to the right to avoid him.</p>

<p>I spun of my own accord on lap 11 and then spun again 3 laps
from the end, that time hitting the wall and forcing a slow crawl
back to the pits, where I still finished 6th, 2 laps down.</p>

<?UMBRACO_MACRO videourl="" videoheight=""
aspectratio="" allowfullscreen="0" videowidth=""
macroAlias="uTube.ClassicPlayer" videoid="3dzG9RCHh5w" />


<p>&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>Race 2</strong></p>

<p>Had an ok start. &nbsp;Nathan Growden nearly cleaned me up on T1
but thankfully ran across the pit lane to avoid contact (and giving
himself a slow down penalty in the process :(). &nbsp;I had little
battle with David Buda in the closing stages of the race but I
didn't have enough speed to make a pass. &nbsp;From there my race
settled down into taking it easy. Knowing I didn't have enough pace
to fight for fourth I cruised around in fifth doing enough to not
lose ground to sixth place.&nbsp;</p>

<?UMBRACO_MACRO videourl="" videoheight=""
aspectratio="" allowfullscreen="0" videowidth=""
macroAlias="uTube.ClassicPlayer" videoid="p3BSQq6iw38" />


<p>&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>Race 3</strong></p>

<p>I enjoyed this race. &nbsp;Starting from fifth I ran well,
battling with Nathan Growden in the opening laps of the race before
settling in behind Robert Orton for basically the duration. I
passed him about mid race by later on my own mistake allowed him to
regain the position. &nbsp;The extremely rapid Pro driver Riku
Alatalo also made it up and passed me. &nbsp;I kept my fifth place
start position at the end of the race thanks to the pole sitter
retiring on lap 22. &nbsp;Good clean racing from me with no
incidents or overly aggressive passes (or attempts at passing).</p>

<?UMBRACO_MACRO videourl="" videoheight=""
aspectratio="" allowfullscreen="0" videowidth=""
macroAlias="uTube.ClassicPlayer" videoid="MWCVmn_gjcY" />


<p>&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>Race 4</strong></p>

<p>Got my 4th round win (6 wins this season) in this race.
&nbsp;Starting from fourth I probably shouldn't have won and the
two lead drivers opened up a decent gap. &nbsp; I had a good battle
with Sam Clark and Christopher M Payne but eventually made it
passed them both. &nbsp;I would have had another incident free race
had Payne not tagged me on the opening corner of the race.</p>

<?UMBRACO_MACRO videourl="" videoheight=""
aspectratio="" allowfullscreen="0" videowidth=""
macroAlias="uTube.ClassicPlayer" videoid="1-xJ2uCURbs" />


<p>&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>Race 5</strong></p>

<p>A decent race from my perspective. &nbsp;Started third behind
Mike Quayle and looked like I might get past him on the opening
lap. I even had a go on turn two, but he got superior drive out of
the corner and took me back down the straight and it was all over.
&nbsp;He and Paul Nelson edged away at about 0.5s per lap and I
took third place. &nbsp;An otherwise eventless race. &nbsp;I
recorded a bit of Andrew Kiss racing, just to get a perspective
from down the back of the grid.</p>

<?UMBRACO_MACRO videourl="" videoheight=""
aspectratio="" allowfullscreen="0" videowidth=""
macroAlias="uTube.ClassicPlayer" videoid="mtbFPehtnsQ" />


<p>&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>Race 6</strong></p>

<p>My final race of the round. Decent SOF and I started 5th, behind
Mike Quayle, again! /sigh. &nbsp;This time he lost it on turn 1 and
I made it by into 3rd, where I sat for a while. &nbsp;The lead
driver eventually lost control of his car and I was into 2nd, where
I stayed until the end of the race :)</p>

<?UMBRACO_MACRO videourl="" videoheight=""
aspectratio="" allowfullscreen="0" videowidth=""
macroAlias="uTube.ClassicPlayer" videoid="JsY_9KT9zkA"
/>]]></bodyText>
