            </articleType>
            <tags><![CDATA[iracing,spa]]></tags>
            <bodyText><![CDATA[
<p>Spa-rring.. Geddit? As in Sparring: what you do when you
practice fighting. ...Annnnyyywaaayyy...</p>

<p>&nbsp;</p>

<p>I threw normal caution out the window for race 1 and raced
without first qualifying. &nbsp;Not the best idea at the best of
times and probably not a great idea at Spa, the track that caused
my downfall last season. &nbsp;Last season, at this track, I went 7
races without finish! I even spun out of the lead twice. &nbsp;</p>

<p>I'm hoping this season, my second in the Mazda powered formula
car, my Spa effort would be better. I was hoping I'd come the
Belgian circuit a more composed and experienced race driver, my
racecraft significantly honed.</p>

<p>I've just done my first race and what a cracker. &nbsp;I started
fourth, the second of the non-qualifiers, behind Jed Jury.
&nbsp;Jury's a familiar face but I haven't raced him much this
season. &nbsp;Most of the field was filled with C class drivers...
&nbsp;Of the line one of those C-class drivers shot it up the
inside into la source, the first corner - a hairpin. &nbsp;</p>

<p>Knowing what a bogey track this was for me last season I left
&nbsp;big gap and stuck way wide: right to the edge. &nbsp;He went
up into fourth position no problem and started battling intensely
with 2nd (another C class and 2nd qualifier) and Jed Jury.
&nbsp;All three were weaving about the track jockeying for
position. &nbsp;All the while I hung back waiting for the
eneviatble incident at the top of the hill. Sure enough, it came
and the two C-class drivers when spearing off into the wall after
colliding with each other!</p>

<p>For the next 8 laps Jed Jury and I had an intense battle as I
run right on his gearbox. &nbsp;Each tour around I noticed he was
significantly slower through the first few corners at the top of
the hill and as I closed right up to him on lap 10 he made a
mistake and I was able to slip through.&nbsp;</p>

<p>I wasn't able to shake him though and after a few more laps I
made another small mistake (no incidents though) through eu rouge
and he got past on top speed down the straight. &nbsp;We again
battled closely but a few laps later he collided with a backmaker
again at the top of the hill and he race was run. &nbsp;From there
it was a completely clear run in 2nd. &nbsp;Mike Quayle (again! :))
was in the lead by about 14 seconds now and I wasn't going to catch
him and 3rd place was half a minute back. &nbsp;</p>

<p>Toward the end Mike had a little slide and lost 4 seconds.
&nbsp;It wasn't enough and I finsihed the race in second place.
&nbsp;Only one incident. Unfortunately it was a pretty low SOF and
I only collected 91 points. &nbsp;9 short of my self prescribed 100
per race goal. &nbsp;Mike collected 99 for the win...</p>
]]></bodyText>
            <teaser><![CDATA[
<p>What a nightmare haha</p>
]]></teaser>
