            <bodyText><![CDATA[
<p>Ever since the 2013 season 1 scheduled was pbublished racing the
Star Mazda was a scary prospect. &nbsp;LRP is one of the two
circuits on the Rookie Road schedule and as such not only is it
well known to every driver, the less experienced drivers all own it
and are therefore more likely to have a crack at the Start Mazda.
&nbsp;</p>

<p>My practice started on Wednesday, trying to find a setup.
&nbsp;Eventually, thanks to my teammates at Vortex I had a decent
baseline, which I then tweaked to my particular, right foot braking
style. &nbsp;</p>

<p>I had two cracks at qualifying, following consistently setting
46.3's in practice. &nbsp;My first effort was a 43.5, which while
not too bad, 0.2s is a lot - about 40 places in the overall
standings. &nbsp;On my second run I did get a 46.3 and that was
enough to put me in the mid 34th out of more than 1500
qualifiers.</p>

<p>Qualifying is one thing, but racing is an entirely different
beast at this super slippery and bumpy circuit. &nbsp;I lined up
for the 7:45am race on Sunday morning my time (+10 GMT) in fourth
place in the top split (out of 43 drivers). &nbsp;My race plan was
to drive well within my limits and to give away places rather than
battle and make mistakes. &nbsp;</p>

<p>Off the start line I maintained 4th and sat there for a few
laps, losing out 3 seconds on 3rd place, then it blew out to 6
seconds as I took it easy, early on the brakes and late on the
throttle. &nbsp;2nd spun himself out of the race and I moved up to
third, with a 10 second advantage back to 4th. &nbsp; 4th (Fabrizio
Raffa) started to catch me at about 0.5s a lap and when he had the
gap down to 7.5s I started increasing my pace, comfortably pulling
the gap back out to 9.5 seconds. &nbsp;2nd place put it in the wall
and then I was in second. &nbsp;10 laps from the end I came across
a lapped car who did his best to block me for 3 laps and I lost 6
seconds to third place. &nbsp;Suddenly he was 3.5 seconds from me
and &nbsp;with 5 laps to go it was on again. &nbsp;</p>

<p>I managed to hold on to second and score 138 points, my best
ever result, and a good one in a 2438 SOF race.</p>
]]></bodyText>
            <teaser><![CDATA[
<p>Rob takes second place at Lime Rock Park and scores a career
high 138 points in an attrition filled race where only 4 of the 17
starters finished. &nbsp;Rob brought his car home from 4th on the
grid with 0 incidents.</p>
]]></teaser>
