            <bodyText><![CDATA[
<p style="text-align: justify;"><img src="/media/1253/season-openersml.png" width="800" height="301" alt="Season Opener sml"/></p>

<p style="text-align: justify;">Season 2 of 2013 kicked off today
and after a successful campaign running the Star Mazda for Vortex
last season, after 4 seasons in the open wheeler I've signed a deal
to drive the GT series with the same team. &nbsp;</p>

<p>I'll be competing in both the GT Challenge series and the Grand
Am series.</p>

<p>In the GT Challenge series the Mclaren MP4/12C runs in the GT3
configuration against the Ford GT GT2 and Corvette C6R. &nbsp;This
will be not only my first closed wheel race series in 2 years,
it'll be my first multi-class race series.</p>

<p>In the Grand Am series the Mclaren lines up against the Riley
MKXX Daytona Prototype, a seriously rapid car. &nbsp;</p>

<p>I've long been a Mclaren fan and to drive a Mclaren is something
special, so I'm really looking forward to this new challenge and to
proving myself across more types of racing.</p>

<p>After the opening practice session at Laguna Seca, I finished
the day in 2nd place with a time of 1:23.447, set on full tanks.
&nbsp;I couldn't go faster on low fuel, so there's some setup work
to do as I learn the car.</p>
]]></bodyText>
            <teaser><![CDATA[
<p>Rob Gray has signed for Vortex Mclaren for the 2013s2 season,
stepping sideways out of the star mazda to race tin-top cars for
the first time.</p>
]]></teaser>
