            <tags><![CDATA[iracing,racecraft]]></tags>
            <bodyText><![CDATA[
<p>Over the seasons on iRacing I've iterated over my approach to
racing in order to ensure I have the least number of incidents.
&nbsp;After last season I have identified a few places where I'm
weak when it comes to racing.</p>

<p>In the past I've always been a right foot braker and taking a
late turn in. &nbsp;To do this I get right out wide and then turn
in sharply, sorting out the rear end as I go. &nbsp;Left foot
brakers tend to turn in earlier and take a more traditional
constant arc through a turn. &nbsp;</p>

<p>I believe my style of cornering encourages drivers to divebomb.
&nbsp;I am led to believe this when last season it seemed I was
attacked this way on a number of occasions and because I tried to
avoid incidents I'd back out of the throttle and let the car past.
&nbsp;</p>

<p>By taking a more defensive and earlier turn-in, following
drivers should be less likely to try and "stick it up the inside"
as they should hopefully note a smaller and earlier decreasingly
smaller gap into each turn. &nbsp;</p>

<p>I've also been subjected to what I would consider unsporting and
ungentleman-like behaviour such as moving to block in the braking
zone and weavng multiple times down the straight to prevent me
passing. &nbsp;At each time these actions really annoyed me, but
everyone approaches racing differently and after the recent
real-life antics of Sebastian Vettel, and the reaction to his
driving style, I think what these drivers are doing is within the
limits of sporting on most occasions.&nbsp;</p>

<p>Pretty much all commentators agree that Vettels style of driving
is the style of true champions. &nbsp;The true greats see an
opportunity and they take it. Damned be the feelings of their
competitors.</p>

<p>I think to make me more competitive I need to be more assertive
when I race, and that definitely includes placinh my car in
positions where drivers feel they have a shot at making a move.</p>
]]></bodyText>
            <teaser><![CDATA[
<p>I've had a good think about my mental approach to racing thus
far and I think I've got some room for approvement. &nbsp;Here's
what my approach to racing this season will be...</p>
]]></teaser>
