            <bodyText><![CDATA[
<p><img src="/media/3582/Indianapolis-RoadCourse.JPG" width="500" height="300" alt="Indianapolis-RoadCourse.JPG" style="float: left;"/>I enjoyed Indianapolis road from the first lap.
&nbsp;It's got a good flow of corners that combine low speed and
high speed corners. &nbsp;Indianapolis road uses a portion of the
classic Indianapolis Oval track, home of the legendary Indy 500,
with an inner road portion, as used by MotoGP and Formula 1.
&nbsp;</p>

<p>The oval portion wants a low downforce stiffly spring setup,
while the twisty inner wants a high downforce softer setup.
Basically it's a compromise. &nbsp;</p>

<p>I started off with the Laguna Seca set and made a few changes to
soften the rear and stiffen the front; the way I have run my Star
Mazda. &nbsp;The handling was pretty much how I wanted it, in that
it was very stable. However, Cyril made the point that such a high
downforce will kill me on the straights and won't give me enough
front end grip, which will punish me over 35 laps. &nbsp;With that
in mind I reduced the rear wing to 5 (from 9).</p>

<p>I managed to do a few laps in the 1:25.9's and to lower my
optimal time to a 1:25.4. &nbsp;Fast, but not super fast.
&nbsp;About where I usually am, even with the Star Mazda. &nbsp;I
was topping, or near topping every practice session. &nbsp;I seem
to have made an improvement from last week, comparative to the rest
of the field.&nbsp;</p>

<p>This weeks race schedule was messed up. &nbsp;I was too tired
(from my 7 month old son crying all night on Thursday night) to
qualifying on Friday, or do any practice laps for that matter. As a
result I qualified on Saturday morning and joined up for the 10am
race. &nbsp;</p>

<p>I qualified 3rd, my worst (and average) position. &nbsp;I was
also immediately behind teammate Cyril Rodriguez, who qualified
0.5s faster than me (my 1:26.0 versus his 1:25.5). &nbsp;I stuck
with him for a few laps, with 2nd place spinning at the first
corner a few laps in. &nbsp;Eventually I started to fall back for a
tenth, then a few tenths, then a second. &nbsp;Once I'd lost that
tow down the straight I couldn't keep up. &nbsp;Even if I had the
pace through the twisty infield (and it seemed I did).</p>

<p>Californian Anthony Bonner was the car ranked just below mine,
and starting a few places back. &nbsp;He made his way quickly to my
rear and by about 10 laps in he was close behind. He had slightly
more pace, especially on the oval portion, where lap after lap I
watched him catch 0.3s per lap, while I would get 0.3 back on him
through the infield.</p>

<p>Soon enough the Corvette drivers caught us to put a lap down. At
this point Cyril was gone, some 10 seconds up the road. &nbsp;We
lost both lost time getting out of the way of overly (in my
opinion) agressive C6R drivers, who muscled their way past.</p>

<p>We raced on lap after lap, for the most part I maintained a
greater than 1.0s advantaged. &nbsp;I really needed that gap.
&nbsp;While these cars don't run DRS (unlike F1), if you get within
1.0's the aero benefits are significant and given Anthony's already
faster straightline speed, if he got a tow, it would be all over
for me.</p>

<p>Eventually he got the tow he needed and about 6 laps from the
end he breezed by into 2nd place just before the braking zone for
turn 1. &nbsp;I sat behind him, within 0.3s until the second lap.
My car was definitely faster through the infield, while he was
quicker down the straight. &nbsp;I managed to hold on to the tow.
&nbsp;</p>

<p>Unfortunately with a lap and a bit to go Scott Wild in fourth
place came up to put us a lap down and I lost 2 seconds getting out
of the way for him. &nbsp;I couldn't make those two seconds up and
I finished 2.3s behind Anythony. &nbsp;With small consolation I was
the 2nd fastest overall single lap, with a 1:26.468, 0.15s behind
Cyrils best. &nbsp;</p>

<p>Both Anthony and I had 0 incidents during the race, and a very
rewarding battle. &nbsp;Overall I was very satisfied with the
result.</p>

<p>The only disappointing thing was the SOF. &nbsp;Because it was
so low (1532) I only socred 78 points. &nbsp;Much less than my
effort for 6th place last week.</p>
]]></bodyText>
