            <bodyText><![CDATA[
<p><img src="/media/3642/Okayama-Full.JPG" width="500" height="305" alt="Okayama-Full.JPG" style="float: left;"/>Round 4 of the GT Challenge series saw us make the
virtual journey to the Land of the Rising sun the the Okayama (AKA
Aidia) crircuit, host of Formula 1 Grand Prix's of the not to
distant past.</p>

<p>Okayama Short is one of two circuits on the Rookie Series (MX5)
rotation, and as such everyone is familiar with it. That also means
it's included in the initial bundle, so everyone owns it. &nbsp;I
expected a large turnout because of this.&nbsp;</p>

<p>The GT Challenge series, with Corvettes, Mclarens, and Ford GT's
aren't particular suited to this thin track. &nbsp;It's not a bad
track but the twisty nature can make it challenging for the
Corvette drivers and challenging for the faster Mclaren drivers who
are immediately behind the, because it is the Mclaren drivers that
have to fight with the slower Corvettes. &nbsp;That was my undoing
on more than one occasion.</p>

<h3>Practice</h3>

<p>As usual, I practiced during the week, up until the weekend.
&nbsp;I managed a few 1:28.9s. &nbsp;At the end of the first days
practice I was doing 1:29.2's and on day two I managed a 1:28.9 and
it never got any faster. &nbsp; The difference between this and
last week, and especially week 1, was the time it took me to get
used to the car. &nbsp;I think I'm pretty much used to the car now.
&nbsp;I'm maybe not super confident with it and I certainly cannot
yet resolve problems using car setup, but I could probably race in
the first few days now.</p>

<h3>Qualifying</h3>

<p>Probably thanks to increased car feel confidence I did my
qualifying session on Thursday night this week and managed a 1:29.0
in the closing stages. &nbsp;Seeing as 1:28.9 was as good as it got
in practice and the 1:29.0 was set on my last lap in qualifying,
having just crossed the line before the flag came out, I thought it
was fast "enough". &nbsp;As it turns out it was good enough for the
rest of the weekend. &nbsp;I didn't always have high strengths of
field, but my worst starting position was 3rd and I got 2 pole
positions.</p>

<h3>Race</h3>

<p><img src="/media/3973/okayama-mp4-races.jpg" alt="2013s02w03"/></p>

<p>The races were "interesting". &nbsp;I was leading race 1, after
closely battling with Chris E Pence for much of the rac.e &nbsp;I
followed him with 0.5s for the first 15 or so laps until he finally
made a big enough mistake on the exit of turn 11 for me to pass
down the straight and into turn 1. &nbsp;Then he sat on my tail by
about the same amount. &nbsp;After about 5 more laps, and feeling
like I had him covered until the end of the race, I got
power-oversteer on the exit of Redman and lost it into the wall.
&nbsp;I thought the damage was minor, as my front left brushed the
concrete fence, but I had 14 minutes of repairs and that was
it.</p>

<p>Race 3 was intrestering in that it was my first time starting
from pole. behind the "faster" Corvettes. &nbsp;I say "faster"
because there were three or four Corvettes doing battle right in
front of me that were very much holding me up. &nbsp;Blocking me
into the corners then using their straight line speed advantage to
pull away down the straights. &nbsp;After about 7 laps three of
them had a coming together and I slowed right down to avoid.
&nbsp;Luckily I did avoid but in the melee I lost not just 1st
place but 2nd. &nbsp;I managed to move into 2nd place again but by
then I'd lost 9 seconds to first, after losing time behind 2nd
place. &nbsp;I eventually closed the gap to first down to 4 seconds
but he had more pace than me anyway. &nbsp;</p>

<p>Race 4 and I was off pole again. &nbsp;I pulled away easily into
the lead, doing 1:28.2 on the third lap. Again the Corvettes held
me up but this time I managed to get through. I was also helped out
by a weaker stength of field. &nbsp;By lap 26 I had built up a 37
second lead over 2nd place, when the lead and 2nd place Corvettes
came to put me a lap down. &nbsp;As usual the lead Corvette tried
to muscle his way through and took us both out of the race!
&nbsp;The 2nd place Vette hit the first placed but managed to go on
to win. &nbsp;I bet Jordan Barris, back in 2nd place in the MP4 was
happy!</p>

<p>&nbsp;</p>
]]></bodyText>
            <teaser><![CDATA[
<p>A twisty, tight track that we're all familiar with. &nbsp;My
first win went begging twice. &nbsp;I can be happy that I was
pretty competitive at this circuit</p>
]]></teaser>
