            <tags><![CDATA[brands hatch,iracing]]></tags>
            <bodyText><![CDATA[
<p><img src="/media/3542/BrandsHatch-GrandPrix.JPG" width="619" height="385" alt="BrandsHatch-GrandPrix.JPG" style="float: left;"/></p>

<?UMBRACO_MACRO videourl="" videoheight=""
aspectratio="" allowfullscreen="0" videowidth=""
macroAlias="uTube.ClassicPlayer" videoid="9vpkwUo99LI" />


<p>It was a long time coming, my first win in the GT Challenge
series. I've come close a few times at the last few circuits.
&nbsp;Notably when I had a 37 second lead in Okayama, only to be
taken out by the lead Corvette. &nbsp;This win wasn't a massive
feat, but I'll take it anyway.</p>

<p>I started of pretty quick from day one at Brands Hatch and I was
closer to my teammates in Qualifying than ever before, and while I
didn't get a lot of race time this weekend, I made it count when it
mattered and secured a 2nd and a 1st, from three starts. I also got
a pole position (and two 2nd place starts).</p>

<h3>Practice</h3>

<p>Practice started on Tuesday night as usual and I took Stephane's
set and worked with that. I only made a few changes, increased the
ABS from 3 to 8, added 2 clicks more fuel, and 1 click more front
tyre pressure (141 kpa). &nbsp;From the tuesday I managed to turn a
1:24.4 in practice, 0.4s faster than the qualifying time Cyril
Rodreguez my own benchmark managed in the MP4/12C in the Grand-Am
series a few weeks ago. &nbsp;It was also only 0.6 behind team
leader Stephane. &nbsp;</p>

<p>I practice for qualifying pace on Tuesday, Wednesday, and
Thursday nights. &nbsp;I didn't better my 1:24.4 but I got into the
1:24.4's a number of times and pushed my optimal down to a
1:23.700.</p>

<h3>Qualifying</h3>

<p>I kept improving through the session and managed a 1:24.345,
just eclipsing my practice best. I'd have gone even faster but I
made a small mistake on the last corner. &nbsp;Ultimately the rest
of the lap was as good as I was ever going to get it, so the small
mistake on the final turn mattered little. &nbsp;</p>

<p>By the end of the week my qualifying time was 67th fastest out
of 206, and 4th fastest in Australia/NZ. I was 0.1s behind my
teammates Christian (#61) and Cyril Rodriguez (#62), who both have
higher iRating's than I do, so it wasn't too bad an effort.</p>

<h3>Race</h3>

<p>I did three races over the weekend, my racing limited by a
weekend long visit by my mother. I raced once on friday, and twice
on Sunday aternoon.</p>

<p><img src="/media/4393/brandshatch-mp4.jpg" alt="Brandshatch-mp4"/></p>

<p><a
href="http://members.iracing.com/membersite/member/EventResult.do?&amp;subsessionid=8334063&amp;custid=59619">
Race 1</a> was good, even if there were only a few MP4's. &nbsp;I
qualified 2nd behind Coppers Laurent, who I know is faster than me
from the Star Mazda series, and he qualified 0.5 faster than I did.
&nbsp;He pulled away at a decent race and finished about half a
minute ahead of me, while I pulled away from third place without a
worry. &nbsp;I got one incident and had an otherwise uneventful
race for 88 points. &nbsp;</p>

<p><a
href="http://members.iracing.com/membersite/member/EventResult.do?&amp;subsessionid=8347589&amp;custid=59619">
Race 2</a> and I started from pole and pulled out a 6.5 second gap
by lap three. &nbsp;Eduardo Prado a few places back, not
qualifying, and with an iRating of (3608) I expected him to carve
through the field. &nbsp;He'd made it into second by lap four and
didnt' seem to be closing much if any, when I came across a spun
Corvette (ranked 15 out of 19 cars, and hte lowest ranked
Corvette). &nbsp;Knowing Corvettes and their impulses to pass
whever they feel like it and seeing this guy was low ranked I moved
over and opened the door for him to pass. &nbsp;We went into turn 5
with me very left and him on the inside. &nbsp;I drove around the
left edge of the track but he drove straight into me and put me
into the wall. &nbsp;The car was bent but I could keep going.
&nbsp;I had a few offs as I tried to deal with the bent steering
but pulled off just after the start of the next lap and
retired.</p>

<p><a
href="http://members.iracing.com/membersite/member/EventResult.do?&amp;subsessionid=8348350&amp;custid=59619">
Race 3</a> and I again started 2nd, this time to Andrew Richardson
a fellow Aussie who I've raced with a bunch in the Star Mazda
series. &nbsp;He qualified 0.2 seconds faster than me. &nbsp;Toward
the end of lap one two Corvettes came together at turn 8 and I was
able to take advantage of Andrew slowing down to avoid collision
and took first place. &nbsp;From there I battled, driving on a
knife edge to stay ahead of Andrew. &nbsp;It seemed like he make a
small mistake and drop 1.0s then catch it up in half a lap.
&nbsp;It seemed he had a lot more pace. &nbsp;However, he lost
control on about lap 8 and his race was done as he dropped first
7.5 second back then spun out of the race a few laps later.
&nbsp;Talking just after he spun, he said he was on the ragged edge
too, trying to keep up &nbsp;with me. I wish I knew that earlier
and I wouldn't have sweated so much :) &nbsp;I went on to win the
race by nearly a full lap over 2nd place. &nbsp; My first victory
in the class!</p>
]]></bodyText>
