            <bodyText><![CDATA[
<p><img src="/media/3912/WatkinsGlen-ClassicBoot.JPG" width="500" height="305" alt="WatkinsGlen-ClassicBoot.JPG" style="float: left;"/>Easily a race to forget. &nbsp;Watkins Glen in the
MP4 started positively, with my first (and only) qualifying attempt
outpacing my two teammates that had qualified at that point, and
putting me 36th overall. &nbsp;The Queens birthday public holiday
fell on the Monday of this week, so I had an extra day of racing.
&nbsp;It was my plan to do as many races as possible this weekend.
Partly because I enjoy this track (or I did enjoy it) and partly
because I had the extra time. &nbsp;</p>

<p>I set a goal to have by the end of the week: an 2500 iRating
again. &nbsp;Starting at high 2300's, it shouldn't have been that
hard. &nbsp;All I needed to do was finish the races in the top 5
and I'd get an increase in time. &nbsp;I figured I would do about
10 races, so that's only around 15 iRating points increase each
race. &nbsp;Easy, given my apparent speed.</p>

<h3>Practice</h3>

<p>Practice started positively. &nbsp;There was no team setup up on
day one so I started with Indianapolis Road and a few tweaks.
&nbsp;I was doing 1:45.5's in the first 30 minutes, good enough for
2nd place in that session. &nbsp;I grabbed the team qualifying
setup on Wednesday (thanks Stephane!) and had at it. &nbsp;1:45.0.
&nbsp;That's pretty decent. &nbsp;The best time I'd seen was a mid
1:44. &nbsp;</p>

<p>I practiced many more times and unfortunately it never got any
faster. &nbsp;I ran my race setup (1 race wing) and was 0.3-0.5s
better than that time on a number of successive laps on Monday, but
every time I'd would put two wheels off-track and get a 1x, even
when I was trying not to. It because very frustrating (so much so
that I pulled over and went to the gym to let off some frustration!
).</p>

<h3>Qualifying and Time Trial</h3>

<p>I qualified on Wednesday night, laying down a 1:44.9. &nbsp;I
made mistake on the next lap, when I was 0.22s up on that time,
giving myself a 1x and invalidating my lap time, but otherwise it
was a good session. &nbsp;</p>

<p>I didn't qualifying again throughout the weekend. &nbsp;By the
end of the week I was ranked 46th in the world. Still probably my
best qualifying result to date in this series. &nbsp;I took 3 poles
from 10 races this week.</p>

<p>This is also my second week and Time Trials and I did a 1:45.777
average over the 4 laps to put myself 2nd in division 3 and 14th
overall. &nbsp;I've now got 166 points from 2 starts, the highest
average points for division 3. &nbsp;If I had done all 6 trials at
that pace, I'd be leading the division and sitting in 5th
overall!</p>

<p>The numbers pointed to a good weekend.</p>

<h3>Race</h3>

<p>Boy was I wrong. &nbsp;Here's my results for the week.</p>

<p><img src="/media/4512/WG-results-mp4.jpg" alt="WG-results-mp4"/></p>

<p><a
href="http://members.iracing.com/membersite/member/EventResult.do?&amp;subsessionid=8395729&amp;custid=59619">
Race 1</a> was good. &nbsp;I drew some of the fastest MP4 drivers
around, and two team members of Brasa (a Brazilian team) in Renato
Silva and Wendel Parra. &nbsp;My teammate Cyril Rodriguez beat them
both this week, but I was nowhere near their pace. &nbsp;I started
4th on the grid and survived a spin that dropped me down 7th to
finish in 5th. &nbsp;Had I not spun I think I had the pace to beat
WIlliam Trajano into 4th. &nbsp;Either way I'm happy with 5th in
the that field, especially considering the average iRating ahead of
me was 3762 versus my iRating of 2300 at the time.&nbsp;</p>

<p><a
href="http://members.iracing.com/membersite/member/EventResult.do?&amp;subsessionid=8396432&amp;custid=59619">
Race 2</a> was not so good. &nbsp;Off the back of the decent
performance in race 1, I hoped to continue to gain iRating in race
2. I was ready on target of 15 iRating or more each race. &nbsp;I
ran around in 2nd place for the first 3 laps, before the pressure
from Anthony Bonner made me push to hard and I lost the rear in the
right hander after the Carousel. &nbsp;As a reult my car was
damaged and I was in last place. &nbsp;I would have stayed last had
not Fernando Avallone crashed with 10 laps to go. &nbsp;I lost 61
iRating</p>

<p>If Race 2 was bad, <a
href="http://members.iracing.com/membersite/member/EventResult.do?&amp;subsessionid=8397130&amp;custid=59619">
Race 3</a> didn't make up for it. &nbsp;From second on the grid I
was hounded by Jonathan Auger on the opening 5 laps, before letting
him by, as I wasn't making an impression on Warrick Sxpak 2 seconds
in front and Warrick was getting away as I drove to try and defend
from Jonathan. &nbsp;My hope was that by letting Auger past, he
would catch Szpak and slow them both down. &nbsp;Unfortunately,
while he did get very close, he never got close enough to bother
him much and they both pulled away from me. &nbsp;My race was done
when I again lost control and dopped back places. &nbsp;Luckily I
was able to make up a few spots and nearly took 4th position across
the line. &nbsp;I lost 10 iRating and was down to 2274.</p>

<p><a
href="http://members.iracing.com/membersite/member/EventResult.do?&amp;subsessionid=8403151&amp;custid=59619">
Race 4</a> didn't promise a lot. &nbsp;I qualified 8th in a very
strong field and my plan was to cruise around and hope I'd get a
place or two through attrition. Fortunately the MP4 leader didn't
leave enough gap to the Corvettes on the opening lap and a massive
crash at turn 1 took out most of the field! &nbsp;I profitted and
ran up in 2nd place for a few laps, before dropping back to 3rd and
driving for the points. In this 2711 field I collected 126 points!
&nbsp;If the week stopped there I'd have been ok. &nbsp;I made 72
iRating to put me back about where I started the week.</p>

<?UMBRACO_MACRO
videourl="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=eyVCT6qd4Fo"
videoheight="" aspectratio="" allowfullscreen="0"
videowidth="" macroAlias="uTube.ClassicPlayer"
videoid="" /> 

<p><a
href="http://members.iracing.com/membersite/member/EventResult.do?&amp;subsessionid=8404576&amp;custid=59619">
Race 5</a>&nbsp;and my first pole position of the week! &nbsp;Off
the grid it seemed good. &nbsp;I'd likely finish in 2nd or 3rd
place and maybe even win. &nbsp;This race also heralded a bad omen.
&nbsp;Peter Dickson. &nbsp;I can't stand racing the guy. &nbsp;I
first met him in Star Mazda last season and he is the main
contributor to me leaving that series. &nbsp;The guy is a bully on
track and and cursing and swearing bogan in the car. &nbsp;He's one
of the those aggressive drivers that'll leave you no room and will
push his way past then run you off track mid corner.
&nbsp;Basically a prick to race with and makes racing not
enjoyable. &nbsp;He raced with all white MP4, and knew nothing of
rolling starts or multi-class racing, so I can only assume this was
his first foray into the series.&nbsp;</p>

<p>As if that wasn't bad enough, I lead the opening lap and left a
7 second gap to the Corvettes. &nbsp;At turn 1 of lap 1 a Corvette
had come off. I came around the Boot on the first lap and a
Corvette appeared to be parked high and dry. &nbsp;He wasn't
parked. He &nbsp;took off exactly at the point I drove past him and
took me straight out of the race and collected 2nd place as well!
&nbsp;Ranked #30 in the field he just drove straight down on the
apex as the MP4 field came around, in a car that was already
ruined. Thank a bunch Tim Allen. Grow a brain! &nbsp;113 iRating
lost (And my nemesis Peter Dickson won the race!)</p>

<?UMBRACO_MACRO
videourl="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=fTm6bjyA-vg"
videoheight="" aspectratio="" allowfullscreen="0"
videowidth="" macroAlias="uTube.ClassicPlayer"
videoid="" /> 

<p>&nbsp;</p>

<p><a
href="http://members.iracing.com/membersite/member/EventResult.do?&amp;subsessionid=8405233&amp;custid=59619">
Race 6</a> and again I started from pole. &nbsp;This could make up
for some of the damage done last race. &nbsp;Chad Chastian
qualified second, 0.003s behidn me. &nbsp;He's quick. Proper quick,
so I didnt have any dellusions of winning this race, but again, I
could have finished high. &nbsp;I made it through turn 1, but Joe
Junior, the number one Corvette Qualified and #2 ranked driver in
the field decided to start from pits to avoid carnage in the
Corvettes. He came steaming out of the pits and hit me as he tried
to go up my inside into turn 2. &nbsp;I had no idea he was there
and certainly wasn't expecting him, as I battled with Chad, making
sure I left him room on the exit of turn 1 and covered him off
through turn 1. &nbsp;</p>

<p>The hit from Joe put me in the wall and bounced back in front of
Chad and took him out too. &nbsp;127 iRating lost! &nbsp;I was down
to 2016 an things were going from bad to worse.</p>

<?UMBRACO_MACRO
videourl="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=j9iMU-dL3FI"
videoheight="" aspectratio="" allowfullscreen="0"
videowidth="" macroAlias="uTube.ClassicPlayer"
videoid="" /> 

<p>&nbsp;</p>

<p><a
href="http://members.iracing.com/membersite/member/EventResult.do?&amp;subsessionid=8405821&amp;custid=59619">
Race 7</a>&nbsp;and I neede to make up for the last few races.
&nbsp;I started 3rd behind Warrick Spazk and Corey Osborne. &nbsp;I
didn't think I could take those two guys, but 3rd would have been
fine. &nbsp;Though Chad Chastian was right behind me, so maybe
fourth!</p>

<p>As it turns out, I didn't have to worry too much. &nbsp;I was
running in 4th position, closely behind Corey Osbourne, after Chad
had taken the lead, 12 laps into the race, when I dropped the rear
and broke the car. My race was done and I lost another 60 iRating.
&nbsp;</p>

<p><a
href="http://members.iracing.com/membersite/member/EventResult.do?&amp;subsessionid=8410535&amp;custid=59619">
Race 8</a>&nbsp;and again I started in 8th in a strong field.
&nbsp;I didn't rate my chaces at all. We had a Pro, Teemu Iivonen
off pole, as well as Wendel Parra, and a bunch of other quick
drivers. &nbsp;Parra spun on the opening corner after being pushed
off track by Tanzi. &nbsp;I spun myself out of the race on lap 4.
&nbsp;Another 39 iRating lost and my iRating was down to 2007.
&nbsp;Things were looking dire and the rot had to stop!</p>

<p><a
href="http://members.iracing.com/membersite/member/EventResult.do?&amp;subsessionid=8412719&amp;custid=59619">
Race 9</a>&nbsp;and this needed to be salvation. &nbsp;I started
from pole, a tenth ahead of Stev Buchheim. &nbsp;We pushed hard
from the start, with Stev sitting close behind as we battled.
&nbsp;In the back of my mind I knew I couldn't afford yet another
crash, so when Stev got hooked up behind down the straight, I
didn't put up a fight into the Carousel. &nbsp;I stayed right and
he took the corner. From there it was all about staying on track
and hopefully staying in second place. I did. &nbsp;+65 iRating -
and I had a good converstaion with a bunch of the guys after the
race. &nbsp;Enjoyable.</p>

<p><a
href="http://members.iracing.com/membersite/member/EventResult.do?&amp;subsessionid=8413371&amp;custid=59619">
Race 10</a> and Monday evening. This was it. The game plan was to
get to the end and to gain iRating. Again, Peter Dickson joined the
race. &nbsp;I really hoped this wasn't going to become a habit,
because I just can't stand the guy. &nbsp;I started from 3rd and
before the end of lap one I had Dickson behind me and we were
battling. &nbsp;Again, I knew I couldn't afford to come off the
track, so I ceeded the place. &nbsp;In reality, he was a little
faster than me in this race. &nbsp;I wasn't lapping as well as I
had been in earlier races. &nbsp;Had I been, I may have won the
race, because my fastest ever race lap was a good few tenths faster
than anyone elses, but I could only get within 0.3 of that lap this
race. &nbsp;</p>

<p>After I let Peter by, I made it past him again down the
straight. I suspect he was running a high DF set, as I breezed by
him like he was standing still. &nbsp;Unfortunately a lap later I
made a meal of that same damn corner as usual, the left hander
after the carousel and I spun. &nbsp;This time I didn't hit
anything and recovered just against of Colin Gorton. &nbsp;Just.
&nbsp;We had a good battle for a few laps until I started to pull
away and catch Chris E Pence. &nbsp;I managed to catch and pass
Chris pretty easily but a few more little errors (no incidents)
allowed him to close the few seconds gap I'd pulled. &nbsp;I
started to close in on Brenton Locke in 4th place but had another
moment. &nbsp; I fiished 5th with 16 more iRating points.</p>

<p>This week saw my iRating drop by a net 280 points. &nbsp;My SR
stayed about the same. While my biggest iRating loses were caused
by other drivers hitting me - the two Corvette cases, I still made
far too many mistakes that cost me podium finishes. &nbsp;Pretty
much all of them at the same corner.&nbsp;</p>

<p>That corner, Chute, turn 6, was my week nemesis. &nbsp;In the
races I did well in I noticed I'd lose between 0.5 and 1.0 each lap
to the cars in front and immediately behind me. &nbsp;I just
couldn't find a way through the turn. It felt awkard to drive and
it seemed my apex was too early, but when I tried to take it
differently I'd lose the back end. &nbsp;A dissappointing weeks
racing.</p>
]]></bodyText>
