            <bodyText><![CDATA[
<p><img src="/media/3617/MidOhio-FullCourse.JPG" width="500" height="315" alt="MidOhio-FullCourse.JPG" style="float: left;"/>This was always going to be a low performing week.
&nbsp;With a family holiday from Friday morning to Sunday
afternoon, track time was going to be restricted. &nbsp;My original
plan was to not race at all...</p>

<h3>Practice</h3>

<p>I started practicing on Monday night, in private test sessions.
&nbsp;There were no existing Vortex sets for Mid Ohio so I made do
as best I could, by taking an existing set and modifying it.
&nbsp;My first attempt saw a low 1:22.2. I was in hosted session
that included Dylan Sharman, Australia's top iRacer (by iRating)
and he was doing 1:19.9's. &nbsp;He had two drivers behind him
doing 1:21.3 and a 1:21.9 respectively. &nbsp;</p>

<p>My teammates at Vortex ended up using my setup. Most of them
expressed their dislike for the track. &nbsp;It's not my favourite
track either and a few of the corners can be quite challenging, but
if you know the track it's not too bad, and I've raced here a fair
bit over the years in a number of different cars (Star Mazda, Skip
Barber, and Mustang).</p>

<p>I eventually got my prctice time down to a 1:21.5. &nbsp;I'm not
sure how I managed that though because the closest I could get at
any point there-after was a 1:21.7, though I was on course to
better it a few times. &nbsp;</p>

<h3>Qualifying</h3>

<p>Given my decent practice time, I had high hopes for qualifying.
&nbsp;I could only manage a 1:21.8 though. &nbsp;Because of my
restricted time I definitely only had the one opportunity...</p>

<p><img src="/media/4533/midohioq.jpg" alt="Midohioq"/></p>

<h3>Race</h3>

<p>Because I had Friday off work I tried two races on Thursday
night but both were unofficial. I did the first race and qualified
first out of four cars. Second on the grid was Warrick Szpak, 0.5
second back. He'd beaten me on merit in three out of three races
last week so it was a good benchmark. I pulled away in the first
two laps then maintained a consistent gap. He must have made a
mistake or dropped off because he went from 1.0 behind me to 5.3s
on about lap 4. From there he lost between half and a full second a
lap as I pulled away. I almost kept up with Nick Jongeneelen's
Corvette in front of me, although it was his first race in the
Corvette! I managed a race best time of 1:22.230 and with an
average race time of 1:24.3, which included two stops of around 40
seconds in total. Most of my laps where between 1:22.8 and 1:23.3,
and my tyres held out well until the end. An informative test run
for official races. Excluding the stop, my average race time was a
1:23.0</p>

<p>I got an official race for the 8am race on Friday morning, my
only shot. I qualified 2nd, behind a PRO driver Antoine Higelin.
Annoyingly, from the start my pedals did not work correctly. I'd
put the power down and get a lag in throttle. Kind of a deadspot in
the pedal where I'd get no power. It was distracting enough to
impact on my lap times, as obviously I'd put the power on at a
certain time with the appropriate amount of steering input and the
car would not turn as I expected. As a result my average lap times
were lower. Had I had the same pedal performance as my unofficial
run I would have finished easily in 2nd place, as Antione's average
lap time was a 1:22.622 and Oliver Poetzl in 2nd place was a
1:24.063</p>

<p>My race was effectively ruined by being bundled up behind
Christopher Albers in the Corvette (with an iRating of 1067 :() -
He was slower than me through the corners, missing almost every
apex, yet because of his massive horsepower advantage he was faster
down the straights and would block me in the corners, leaving me
helpless as a queue of Mclarens formed up behind me. Pablo Pohlmann
(iR:3150) was the first to have a go and he pulled up alongside
enough to make the move stick and I left him through. He eventually
came unstuck on the 2nd last turn. Oliver Poetzl sat bottled up
behind me for many laps, lacking the outright speed to get by. He
had a couple of aborted looksup the inside before he got brave into
turn 8 near the end of the race and punted me off the track,
courtesy of a rear end tap. That was me out of 2nd and down to 6th.
I fortunately recovered to 5th when another driver came off.
However, 2nd should have been mine. I was unhappy with the move
Oliver pulled off because it reeked of desparation, and I let him
know as much.</p>

<p><img src="/media/4538/midohior.jpg" alt="Midohior"/></p>
]]></bodyText>
