            <bodyText><![CDATA[
<p><img src="/media/3722/PhillipIsland.JPG" width="500" height="310" alt="PhillipIsland.JPG" style="float: left;"/></p>

<p>I've been looking foward to my home race all season.
&nbsp;Finally, with week 9, the GT Challenge series arrived at
Phillip Island.</p>

<h4>Practice</h4>

<p>Even though I started practice here on Tuesday, I didn't get a
chance to practice as much as I'd have liked, because I raced in
the Grand Am event on Thursday, so I practiced for taht on
Wednesday and Thursday, leaving my only practice for Friday night.
&nbsp;There also was no Vortex setup, so I made my own. &nbsp;</p>

<p>I managed a 1:29.9 on Tuesday but Aaron Heap was doing 1:28.6's
and my teammates managed 1:29.1's in Qualifying. &nbsp;By the end
of the week my PB was a 1:29.4 with an opt of 1:28.8 and a few
times I was up on my opt near the end before coming off. &nbsp;I
went to bed late Friday night confident of a good setup for the
race and qualifying.</p>

<p>I also put in a few hours of practice between Race 1 and Race 2,
trying to find out what went wrong.</p>

<h4>Qualifying</h4>

<p>After a late Friday night on setup work I woke on Saturday with
only 5 hours sleep and was a lot tired. &nbsp;The best lap I could
manage was a 1:30.0 and that was with my Tuesday setup. The setup
that worked so well the night before could barely keep me on track.
It felt terrible. &nbsp;</p>

<p>Monday night I did Time Trials and for that I changed my setup
by stiffening the front springs. That gave me an immediately better
feel and I turned a 1:29.2. I then did the 7:30pm qualifying
session and turned a couple of 1:29.8's to improve on my 1:30.0.
&nbsp;I didn't do any more races though, so it was moot.</p>

<p><img src="/media/5499/PI-Q-2013s2.jpg" alt="PI-Q-2013s2"/>&nbsp;</p>

<h4>Race</h4>

<p>Race 1, What a distaster. &nbsp;I qualified on pole by a few
tenths and was ranked #5, with #6 in 2nd. &nbsp;He shadowed me for
the first 10 laps and I couldn't really shake him. I was taking it
easy and the only time I could get a gap up was when he'd make a
mistake, and then he'd close up again. &nbsp;I was lappig a
terribly slow GT car when I messed it up and went off track,losing
the lead and 6 seconds. From there it just got worse as I struggled
to stay on track. I was running Hard brake pads and I think that
was part of my problem. &nbsp;I was also pretty physically tired
from a lack of sleep thanks to working on setup the night
before.</p>

<p>I spent most of Saturday following Race 1 feeling down.
&nbsp;The more I practiced the worse I got, to the point where I
couldn't even set a completely mistake free lap! &nbsp;I gave up
and went and watched a movie, resigning myself to not racing the
rest of the day. &nbsp;</p>

<p>The movie watched and coffee consumed I was feeling a bit better
and I couldn't let it end there. &nbsp;I had to solve this
performance problem, be it setup or the way I was driving. &nbsp;I
decided to enter the 4pm race and just cruise around, collecting
what points I could.</p>

<p><img src="/media/5519/PI-WIN.png" width="800" height="301" alt="PI-WIN"/></p>

<p>To my surprise I started from pole, with the other 7 Mclarens in
the field not setting a time. &nbsp;Though right behind me in 2nd
place was non other than Shane Van Gisbergen, V8supercar superstar
- from the real seires, not the iRacing version. &nbsp;I knew I
wasn't going to beat him so I let him go on the start - or rather
he made a cracking start and was gone. &nbsp;He pulled away at an
average of nearly 1.0 seconds a lap while I fought with a host of
drivers. First Zoltan Herczeg had was behind, but couldnt' keep it
on track, then Nigel Baines came up close, but he too dropped back
in spurts. &nbsp;</p>

<p>On lap 16 Van Gisbergen dropped his right rear off the track and
was into the wall and out of the race and I was into the lead.
&nbsp;I led the remaining 14 laps to my second victory of the
season, making up for my mistakes in the first race. &nbsp;This
race was also very strange in that only myself and Nigel finished.
&nbsp;The other 6 drivers all crashed out.</p>

<p>It was cool though, to sit behind SVG and watch his lines.
&nbsp;They weren't much different but I did pick a few little
points up. &nbsp;It's just cool for a motorsport fan to be in the
same race, and to be the position behind, someone as fast in both
real life and virtual racing :)</p>

<p><img src="/media/5504/PI-R-2013s2.jpg" alt="PI-R-2013s2"/></p>
]]></bodyText>
            <teaser><![CDATA[
<p>I've been looking foward to my home race all season.
&nbsp;Finally, with week 9, the GT Challenge series arrived at
Phillip Island. &nbsp;Qualifying and the first race weren't as good
as I expected, but I got a pleasant surprise in the second
race.</p>

<p><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>
]]></teaser>
