            <tags><![CDATA[suzuka,iracing]]></tags>
            <bodyText><![CDATA[
<p><img src="/media/3852/Suzuka-GrandPrix.JPG" width="454" height="291" alt="Suzuka-GrandPrix.JPG" style="float: left;"/>Suzuka is a story of nearly but not quite. &nbsp;A
place where I made a few too many mistakes that cost me valuable
points.</p>

<h4>Practice</h4>

<p>After the problems at Phillip Island Suzuka got off to a good
start. &nbsp;I was immediately faster than the few drivers who were
significantly faster than me at Phillip Island on day 1 of
practice. &nbsp; I was turning 2:02.1's &nbsp;after the first hour
of practice. &nbsp;</p>

<p>Cyril R shared his setup on the team forums and tried that going
forward from Wednesday, with my fastest pratice lap being a
2:01.765, still a way down on Cyril and Christrians though. &nbsp;I
set that time on the Wednesday and didn't better it all week.
&nbsp;There wasn't anything that felt horribly wrong with my car
and I did get my optimal down to 2:00.7, I just couldn't string a
full lap together at near that pace. &nbsp;I came close a number of
times but lost it in either the hairpain (turn 11) or through Spoon
(turn 13).</p>

<h4>Qualifying &amp; Time Trial</h4>

<p>I think qualifying went ok. My fastest lap was looking at being
almost sub 2:01, but again, I made a mess of it, I think through
Spoon. &nbsp;I ended up with a 2:01.509.</p>

<p><img src="/media/5648/Suzi_Q.jpg" alt="Suzi_Q"/></p>

<p><img src="/media/5653/Suzi_TT.jpg" alt="Suzi_TT"/></p>

<h4>Race</h4>

<p><strong>Race 1</strong> definitely did not live up to the hype.
&nbsp;I started from 2nd on the grid, behind Japanese driver
Takafumi Ichikawa, whom I've race a bit but not that often so I
figured he's probably here because it's a Japanese track and he's
Japanese, rather than to continue his championship, like most of
us. &nbsp;Close behind me was Manu Heikkila, who after pushing me
off at Road America, is not my favourite driver. &nbsp;Honestly the
way he drives makes me nervous, which usually means I crash.
&nbsp;Ironic, because I'm nervous about him crashing into me, so I
crash myself out.</p>

<p>Anyway, we parade around and out of the hairpin I'm ahead of
Takafumi and I back off, so I don't take the lead when I shouldn't.
&nbsp;He's going VERY slow. Then he gasses it up and by the time
I've reacted Manu has gone through as well, right behind him and
I'm third. &nbsp;I had more speed than Manu in the race and
probably enough to take Takafumi, but I dropped it at Spoon and put
myself 5 laps down. &nbsp;BThe best I could manage was 6th place,
the last of the finishers. &nbsp;Still, only 2 incidents, so my SR
went up.</p>

<p><strong>Race 2</strong> and I hoped Race 1 would be erased by a
good result here. &nbsp;Again I was 2nd on the grid, with Manu
directly behind me, 2 places back. &nbsp;I made a decent start and
was running close behind Stefan when on the 2nd lap I came unstuck
on turn 7. &nbsp;I limped back to the pits but was many laps down
when I came out and my car was undriveable. &nbsp;I retired.
&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>Race 3&nbsp;</strong> and surely this had to be better.
I started 4th, behind 3rd place Takafumi, with Manu 2 places behind
me. &nbsp;I got away solidly. &nbsp;Nigel Baines made a cracking
start from pole to pull ahead of the three cars behind him that
included me. &nbsp;We battled closely and there was nothing in it.
&nbsp;Nigel had an off and we went past, with him rejoining in 4th
place. &nbsp;The lap later I spun and Nigel collected me. &nbsp;He
retired and I kept going, with a slightly bent car, eventually
rcovering to finish 5th after closing the gap to the top four
drivers. &nbsp;At least my fastest lap was faster than the four in
front. &nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>Race 4</strong> and I qualified 4th with the superfast
Chad Chastian off pole. &nbsp;I didnt' expect much here. &nbsp;I
was right behind Takafumi off 3rd. &nbsp;I'm not sure what happened
but Chad must have fell off pretty early (he retired on lap 12),
because for most the race it was me sitting less than 0.5s from
Takafumi's rear wing. &nbsp;I lacked the pace to overtake and it
seemed whenever he made a small mistake I would do the same.
&nbsp;All in all it was a great fun battle, with the intensity
reflected in how close our fastest laps were (0.009s apart in
favour of Takafumi). &nbsp;Takafumi made a mistake on the 3rd last
lap coming out of Spoon. I tried to capitalise but I took ran wide
and lost 2.0s. &nbsp;From there I knew I wouldn't be able to pass
again, even if I managed to get hooked back up to his rear wing
before the race was done. &nbsp;I instead slowed down to a cruise,
with 30 seconds back to 3rd place there was little change I'd
finish anywhere but 2nd. &nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>Race 5</strong>&nbsp;was a huge field in terms of pace.
&nbsp;I qualified 7th and it looks like this time Manu requalified
because he started one position ahead of me. &nbsp;I made a decent
start but then Manu ran wide into the hairpin on the first lap and
I swerved to miss him as he rejoined. &nbsp;We touched, with me
getting a 0x but the touch allowed the car behind me to take the
spot. &nbsp;A few laps later I spun myself around at Spoon and
narrowly avoided collecting another car as rejoined the track, but
I was back in 2nd last. &nbsp;One of the front runners disconnected
with 6 laps to go and I managed to overtake the very erratic
Leandro S Schmidt for 7th place before the end, but only because he
lost control exiting the final corner of the final lap.</p>

<p><img src="/media/5658/Suzi_R.jpg" alt="Suzi_R"/></p>

<p>&nbsp;</p>
]]></bodyText>
            <teaser><![CDATA[
<p>Suzuka is a story of nearly but not quite. &nbsp;A place where I
made a few too many mistakes that cost me valuable points.</p>
]]></teaser>
