            <tags><![CDATA[Road Atlanta]]></tags>
            <bodyText><![CDATA[
<p><span style="font-size: 1em;"><span style="font-size: 1em;"><img src="/media/3742/RoadAtlanta-Full.JPG" width="475" height="304" alt="RoadAtlanta-Full.JPG" style="float: left;"/></span></span></p>

<h4>Practice</h4>

<p>The week started strong. I took my Suzuka setup and changed it
just slightly and did a few laps and was immediately fast, posting
a low 1:20.3 in practice. &nbsp;&nbsp;</p>

<p>I did a few practice sessions more during the week, particularly
on Wednesday with Anthony and Cyril from Vortex and Iw as
consistently faster than both of them. &nbsp;Although I think
neither were familiar with Road Atlanta, so it was only a matter of
time before they got faster. &nbsp;Something I never did.</p>

<p>Aaron Heap set a 1:19.7 in practice, and shared his set, so I
grabbed that and on Thursday started playing with it and managed to
get my time down to a 1:20.1 and then a 1:20.0 while following a
faster driver (tow) which gave me a 4km/hr boost down the
straight.</p>

<h4>Qualifying</h4>

<p>Given my initial strong practice I qualified on Tuesday night
and immediately set the fastest time in the world at that point.
Small thing though and by the end of the week I'd be nowhere in the
overall standings and Patrick Valente Ferro would have posted a
1:18.477, some 1.7 seconds faster than my best of 1:20.121 (52nd in
the world)</p>

<p><img src="/media/5757/RAt_Q_.jpg" alt="RAt_Q"/></p>

<p>&nbsp;</p>

<p>Time Trial was a little better. I managed a 1:20.7 average which
on my 2nd run. &nbsp;The first run was terrible (1:21.4 avg) due to
not having my load cell set correctly. Once fixed, my times dropped
to what I expected. &nbsp;It was good enough to put me well clear
at the top of Division 3 (my division) by over a second, and to put
me 6th overall.</p>

<p><img src="/media/5752/RAt_TT.jpg" alt="RAt_TT"/></p>

<h4>Race</h4>

<p><strong>Race 1</strong> was a disaster. &nbsp;I got up for the
6am race, hoping to race with my French teammates. &nbsp;I made the
topsplit but didn't qualify highly. &nbsp;I was too tired to keep
focused and my race became a litany of mistakes before I pulled
over and retired and went to work. &nbsp;I just couldn't get my
foot to come smoothly off the brake and as a result I kept losing
the back end. Not cool.</p>

<p><strong>Race 2</strong> was not a whole lot better. I got away
ok but was touched coming up the hill after turn 1. The touch bent
my suspension but at least the car that moved across on me (Nikos)
took out three cars behind me when he came off. &nbsp;I left room
for him to come up the inside on turn one and I kept my speed up
the hill and was just ahead into turn 2, which is barely a turn. I
knew the car to my right would either have to yield to make turn 3
or he'd go off. He moved left to take the turn, and touched me
slightly enough to put bend my steering and make the car handle
poorly for the rest of the race, and I lost about 1.5 seconds a
lap. &nbsp;He though came off the track and three other cars
following close behind hit him ruining all their races. &nbsp;From
the replay it looked like he didn't see me there and certainly I
couldn't see me on my center screen when in his car, so if he only
had once screen and wasn't running a super high FOV (unlikely) he'd
have not know I was there. &nbsp;Racing incident, oh well...</p>

<p><strong>Race 3</strong> and I was on pole by 0.6s in a huge
field of 35 cars and I think 23 Mclarens. &nbsp;Problem was I was
doing development work on a fuel calculator just prior and was
using my Xbox controller and had auto gears and brake and throttle
assists turned on and forgot to turn them off. &nbsp;As a result I
was terribly slow off the line and about 4 seconds off my pace (of
mid 1:20's) until I got used to the car. &nbsp;By then I was down
in 5th place, where I stayed for the remained of the race.</p>

<p><strong>Race 4</strong>&nbsp;was better. This time I started
from 2nd place, with 1st just 0.2s ahead on pole. &nbsp;I made a
decent start and first pulled away easily so I settled into 2nd
place and trying to stay ahead of Trevor Forester. &nbsp;We battled
really well all race, with less than 1.0s between us until he spun
on the exit of turn 5 and lost 7 seconds. &nbsp;</p>

<p><img src="/media/5762/RAt_R.jpg" alt="RAt _R"/></p>

<p>&nbsp;</p>

<p>More annoyingly, I was registered for other races during the
week that didn't go official. &nbsp;I disconnected from the last 2
before the race began and d/c'd from the first one after I made a
mistake (3x). &nbsp;Each race had 9 drivers, so was so close.
&nbsp;One more driver in any class and I've scored some good points
and good iRacing. Note the SOF</p>

<p><img src="/media/5767/RAt_R_NOF.jpg" alt="RAt _R_NOF"/></p>

<p>&nbsp;</p>
]]></bodyText>
            <teaser><![CDATA[
<p>A disapointing week were I didn't get any faster and had pretty
poor races.</p>
]]></teaser>
