            <bodyText><![CDATA[
<p>Steve Meyers has just published the release notes for latest
build, set to drop at the start of next week, July 23rd.&nbsp; The
summary is as follows:</p>

<ul>
<li>Lotus 49 on the NTMv5 (New Tyre Model version 5)</li>

<li>Montreal circuit (Gilles Villeneuve)</li>

<li>Ghost car with 5 different modes</li>

<li>Head Mechanic role who can modify your car setup</li>

<li>Variable weather in hosted and test sessions (still no
rain)</li>

<li>Other big fixes and tweaks to various cars including NTMv5 on
the Skip Barber car and Street Stock</li>

<li>Tech Tracks (draft releases of tracks)</li>
</ul>

<p>There are other cool features too, mainly for leagues, but I
don't think that will impact many racers, as most who do compete in
private leagues seem to use software personalised to each league
(see omr.com.au for example).</p>

<p>A ghost car is now included.&nbsp; iRacing call this the
'<strong>reflap car</strong>'.&nbsp; While the ghost car features
seem out of place in a true simulation, ghosts provide an excellent
way to analyse your own best lap, as far as driving lines and
braking points are concerned.</p>

<p>Variable Weather has been introduced to hosting sessions. This
is a major thing for iRacing, as it was previously big complaint
point from members.&nbsp; Note it's not rain effects, just variable
temperature and fog. It's getting close though</p>

<p>The team features are pretty cool.&nbsp; Previously "crew
chiefs" could change your black box information.&nbsp; Now team
members can adjust your car setup while it's in the garage.</p>

<blockquote>
<p>This build introduces the ability for your teammates to help out
with setting up your car in<br />
 the garage. Apply whatever term fits your mental model for this;
possibly "head mechanic",<br />
 though internally we call this person the "garage editor". As with
the crew chief, any of<br />
 your teammates can take-on and give-up the garage editor role at
will, but only one person may<br />
 claim that role at any given time.<br />
 You can envision visiting the garage screen as picking up a
clipboard that has the team's<br />
 setup sheet on it. In order to make any changes, you need to
request that you become the<br />
 team's "garage editor", and that the team's car be physically put
into the garage, where the<br />
 mechanics can flail away at it with tools, and the effects of any
updates can be measured.<br />
 You do this by clicking the green "edit" icon near the upper-right
corner of the garage<br />
 screen. If you are the only person on your team that is connected
to the session, the "edit"<br />
 button is automatically clicked for you. If the icon is gray, then
the car is forbidden from<br />
 being placed into the garage (generally after a race session
starts).<br />
 While the car is in the garage, the [Drive] button on the session
screen will be disabled, and<br />
 will be shown as [Garage], instead. The helmet and name of the
person that is adjusting the<br />
 car is displayed on the garage screen to all the team's members.
All of the teammates can see<br />
 the changes the garage editor is making to the car's setup each
time the setup finishes "tech<br />
 inspection". Many changes tech quickly and are automatically sent,
but some require the<br />
 [Apply] button to be clicked, or for the [Apply] to be
automatically executed.<br />
 All changes to the team's car setup are tentative, and will only
be committed when the garage<br />
 editor clicks the garage screen's [Done] button. Clicking on this
button relinquishes the<br />
 garage editor role, and physically releases the team's car from
the garage with the latest<br />
 changes applied to it. The garage editor can discard any changes
they've made and revert to<br />
 the team's car as it entered the garage by clicking [Cancel], the
"edit" icon, or [X] to close<br />
 the garage screen, and then confirming that the changes are to be
thrown away. Discarding the<br />
 changes from having clicked the "edit" icon or the [X] will also
give up the garage editor<br />
 role.</p>
</blockquote>
]]></bodyText>
