            <tags><![CDATA[iRacing,Lotus 49]]></tags>
            <bodyText><![CDATA[
<p>It's been a long time coming. &nbsp;The Lotus 49 was announced
last year and was due to be in the season 1 build for 2013.
&nbsp;It didn't make that build, with Dave Krammer, it's main
creator wanting to perfect the physics before release.</p>

<p><img src="/media/6083/250px-Grand_Prix_Legends_Coverart.jpg" width="100" height="116" alt="Grand Prix Legends" style="float: left;"/>For those not iRacing mad (those poor
poor boring souls). &nbsp;Dave made his name on Grand Prix Legends
(well, really made his name there). &nbsp;Some, nay many, consider
GPL to be the first real sim. &nbsp;Unfortunately for me I'd just
started Uni when it debutted when I was brain deep in serious
tertiary education, from which I didn't emerge until many years
later. &nbsp; I heard about GPL but given my
<strong>addiction</strong> to Geoff Crammands Grand Prix series
through the early and mid 90's and my early highschool, I thought
it best I don't get distracted. &nbsp;Wikipedia (for all it's
worthlessness) even says "is considered by many people to be on tof
the most realistic racing games ever released". &nbsp;</p>

<p>With that in mind, it's understandable why Dave felt the Lotus
49 in iRacing, the current "Best racing game of all time" (as voted
by gamers and journalists) should be mint. &nbsp;</p>

<p>The car was delayed again for Season 2 2013, but finally it is
here. And let me tell you it is brilliant but very difficult to
drive. &nbsp;It move about on the road like nothing else. &nbsp;If
you stab at the throttle it'll power oversteer you into a firey
virtual death. If you are abrubt on the brakes you'll lock the
wheels and either have the back come round on you or slide off the
track. &nbsp;&nbsp;</p>

<p>The way to drive this car is with smooth inputs. &nbsp;It was
tyriple world champion Jackie Stewart, who drove Formula 1 during
the Lotus 49 period, who described driving like there's an egg
under the throttle. &nbsp;He also famously related that we should
never get on the throttle until we intended to not get off it.
&nbsp;</p>

<p>I've spent about an hour so far acclimatising to the madness and
joy of this vehicle and this is all I've got to show for it.</p>

<?UMBRACO_MACRO videourl="" videoheight=""
aspectratio="" allowfullscreen="0" videowidth=""
macroAlias="uTube.ClassicPlayer" videoid="dsc3Q2VXoiM" />


<p>When I logged into iRacing this morning there were approximately
4500 people online. In my 2.5 years of iRacing I've never seen so
many people online at once. And another first, every Lotus 49
practice session was near capacity. &nbsp;</p>

<p>Now that the car is finally here and we can stop asking about
it's arrival and complaining of it's tardiness in turning up in our
garages, we are all very excited. &nbsp;Now if only the other
drivers would stay on track and give me a clean lap.</p>

<p>Enough of this, I'm off to get some more practice in!</p>
]]></bodyText>
