            <bodyText><![CDATA[
<p><img src="/media/3727/RoadAmerica-Road.JPG" width="500" height="315" alt="RoadAmerica-Road.JPG" style="float: left;"/>I had a little more time to practice / race this
week, as I had all week off work. &nbsp;I began practicing on
Wednesday and actually qualified and raced that day, doing the
12:45 and 2:45 pm races.&nbsp;</p>

<p>I think I did two practice sessions this week, as I already know
this track and go well here. &nbsp;</p>

<h4>Qualifying</h4>

<p>My initial qualifying attempt of 2:07.7 was very ordinary, but
it was enough to keep getting me pole positions until I requalified
on Thursday evening. &nbsp;I did a record 5 qualifying sessions
this week, as a strove for a time I knew I was capable of. &nbsp;By
Thursday night I had qualified with a 2:06.244, a time which at the
time put be 21st overall. &nbsp;And almost always good enough for
pole. &nbsp; The time ultimately put me 30th, the fastest of the
Vortex drivers :)</p>

<p>&nbsp;</p>

<p><img src="/media/6272/roadamerica_q_res.png" width="489" height="29" alt="Roadamerica _q _res"/></p>

<p>&nbsp;</p>

<h4>Time Trial</h4>

<p><img src="/media/6277/road_america_time_trial.png" width="254" height="391" alt="Road _america _time _trial" style="float: left;"/></p>

<p><img src="/media/6282/road_america_time_trial_yay.png" width="500" height="60" alt="Road_america_time_trial_yay"/><br />
<br />
 I had two time trial attempts too, and this is where I did very
well. &nbsp;I ended up with the
fastest&nbsp;<strong>overall</strong>&nbsp;time trial time, even
though I made errors on two laps, by way of setting a 2:06.200 on
my opening lap and then two more laps under 2:07.00</p>

<h4>Race</h4>

<p>Over the week I did 9 races, with a fantastic 5 wins from 7 pole
positions. &nbsp;What did I do differently this week? &nbsp;I think
it's the race start time. &nbsp;It's almost certainly that. I was
home off work this week and could race during the day. The splits
at that time were a good bit lower than my usual splits of
1800-1900, coming in at about 1500-1600. &nbsp;Combined with my
great qualifying time meant I was starting from pole often and
could make the break early on and hold it.</p>

<p>I started the opening race from pole, and on the second lap
Thomas Pendergrass came to make a move on me. &nbsp;Being a long
race, I braked early and let him through, but he lost it on the
exit of the corner and veered right and into me, then the out of
place Riley behind me hit me in the rear and I was out of the
race.</p>

<?UMBRACO_MACRO
videourl="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=-eTBvjbbTNo"
videoheight="" aspectratio="" allowfullscreen="0"
videowidth="" macroAlias="uTube.ClassicPlayer"
videoid="" /> 

<p>I won race 2 easily. &nbsp;In race 3 I qualified 2nd with Manu
Heikkila on pole and Anthony Bonner behind me. &nbsp;I made a
mistake on the last corner of the warm up lap and went wide, givin
the spot to Anthony. &nbsp;From there I got stuck battling with a
DP who couldn't drive. &nbsp;</p>

<?UMBRACO_MACRO
videourl="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=J6TsFulrUxU"
videoheight="" aspectratio="" allowfullscreen="0"
videowidth="" macroAlias="uTube.ClassicPlayer"
videoid="" /> 

<p><a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=J6TsFulrUxU"></a>I won
Race 4 at a canter, by over a minute from 2nd place Jack
Veletanlic.</p>

<p>Race 5 was a strong race and I qualified 4th (would have been
2nd with my time from later in the day!) There was some crazyness
at the end of the warm up lap and myself and 5th place spun out.
&nbsp;I could have stayed left more, but it was close as to who
caused that one. &nbsp;2nd and 3rd also came together in the same
way on the same corner, right in front (which may have contributed
to our accident). &nbsp;From there there was a whole bunch of fail
that made the race interesting, as various drivers dropped out. I
ended up 4th overall anyway...</p>

<?UMBRACO_MACRO
videourl="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=-loeUXnc6bI"
videoheight="" aspectratio="" allowfullscreen="0"
videowidth="" macroAlias="uTube.ClassicPlayer"
videoid="" /> 

<p>I won Race 6 by about 25 seconds. &nbsp;</p>

<p>Race 7 I finished 2nd to Joel Tremblay in a race I should have
won. &nbsp;I led from pole but he nailed it out of the last turn on
the formation lap and was past me before we crossed the line. From
there I sat behind him for the first few laps before I slid off and
hit the wall on the exit of the final turn. &nbsp;I recovered in
5th and made my way back to 2nd place, closing to within 3 seconds
of Joel before losing it again, my car not handling the best. I
rejoined 12 seconds back and closed back in to within 6 seconds,
with 5 laps to go, I would have got him, then I came off again, and
cruised to the end.</p>

<p>I won a very intense Race 8. &nbsp;I started from pole with Joel
in second place. &nbsp;Remembering the last time we met, I covered
the line and got on the throttle early and kept the lead. &nbsp;We
were a second or so apart for a few laps but I manged to pull 0.5s
a lap pretty consistently. I ran a near perfect race, missing I
think only 2 apexes the entire race. By the end I soaked with
sweat, my glasses were fogging, and I was elated. I had a chat with
Joel after and he was the same, he said he gave it everything he
had and was exhausted :D &nbsp;Great race.</p>

<p>I wasn't going to race again but I decidede to jump on for a
final race on Sunday evening. I again started from pole with a big
gap to 2nd place according to the qualifying times. &nbsp;Naruko
Ishida pushed me hard at the start but eventually my consistency
prevailed as I pulled away a bit at a time each lap. &nbsp;I
finished the race about 9 seconds clear of the eventual second
place driver, Johnnie Jones. &nbsp;Another hard fought and
satisfying win.</p>

<p><img src="/media/6331/ra_r_res.PNG" alt="Ra_r_res"/></p>
]]></bodyText>
